He was despised, and we did not care.

487
00:27:51,610 --> 00:27:53,310
Yet it was our weakness he carried.

488
00:27:53,690 --> 00:27:55,650
It was our sorrows that weighed him down,

489
00:27:55,650 --> 00:27:58,330
and we thought his troubles were a punishment from God

490
00:27:58,330 --> 00:27:59,470
for his own sins,

491
00:27:59,850 --> 00:28:01,630
but he was wounded and crushed

492
00:28:01,630 --> 00:28:03,190
for our sins.

493
00:28:04,430 --> 00:28:05,730
Who are we talking about here?

494
00:28:06,820 --> 00:28:07,200
Jesus.

495
00:28:09,380 --> 00:28:10,400
Written in the book of Isaiah

496
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:11,120
in the Old Testament.

497
00:28:11,680 --> 00:28:13,600
He was beaten that we might have peace.

498
00:28:13,860 --> 00:28:15,980
He was whipped and we were healed.

499
00:28:16,880 --> 00:28:18,780
All of us have strayed away like sheep.

500
00:28:18,920 --> 00:28:20,100
We have left God's paths

501
00:28:20,100 --> 00:28:21,100
to follow our own.

502
00:28:21,360 --> 00:28:22,580
Yet the Lord laid on him

503
00:28:22,580 --> 00:28:25,040
the guilt and the sin of us all.

504
00:28:25,990 --> 00:28:28,030
He was oppressed and treated harshly.

505
00:28:28,610 --> 00:28:29,710
Yet he never said a word.

506
00:28:29,710 --> 00:28:31,650
He was led as a lamb to the slaughter.

507
00:28:32,190 --> 00:28:34,110
And as a sheep is silent before the shearers,

508
00:28:34,310 --> 00:28:35,630
he did not open his mouth.

509
00:28:36,030 --> 00:28:38,530
From prison and trial, they led him away to his death.

510
00:28:38,750 --> 00:28:40,370
But who among the people realized

511
00:28:40,370 --> 00:28:42,110
that he was dying for their sin,

512
00:28:42,350 --> 00:28:44,350
that he was suffering their punishment?

513
00:28:45,310 --> 00:28:47,850
He had done no wrong and had never deceived anyone.

514
00:28:48,010 --> 00:28:49,250
But he was buried like a criminal.

515
00:28:49,590 --> 00:28:51,250
He was put in a rich man's grave.

516
00:28:51,310 --> 00:28:52,390
If you know the story of Jesus,

517
00:28:52,970 --> 00:28:53,870
that's exactly what happened.

518
00:28:55,450 --> 00:28:57,430
But it was the Lord's good plan to crush him

519
00:28:57,430 --> 00:28:58,530
and fill him with grief.

520
00:28:58,530 --> 00:29:03,630
Yet when his life is made an offering for sin, he will have a multitude of children, many heirs.

521
00:29:03,830 --> 00:29:07,270
He will enjoy a long life, and the Lord's plan will prosper in his hands.

522
00:29:07,530 --> 00:29:10,810
When he sees all that is accomplished by his anguish, he will be satisfied.

523
00:29:11,590 --> 00:29:16,950
And because of what he has experienced, my righteous servant will make it possible for many to be counted righteous,

524
00:29:17,070 --> 00:29:18,930
for he will bear all their sin.

525
00:29:20,220 --> 00:29:25,380
I will give him the honors of one who is mighty and great, because he exposed himself to death.

526
00:29:25,380 --> 00:29:27,840
He was counted among those who were sinners.

527
00:29:28,260 --> 00:29:32,400
He bore the sins of many, and he interceded for sinners.

528
00:29:34,050 --> 00:29:42,810
If that is not the most graphic depiction, description of Jesus at the week of the passion where he suffered and died,

529
00:29:43,070 --> 00:29:44,810
I don't know what else it is.

530
00:29:45,070 --> 00:29:49,150
And there it is in the Old Testament before Jesus was even born.

531
00:29:51,260 --> 00:29:52,260
How do we account for that?

532
00:29:55,310 --> 00:29:56,270
What are the chances?

533
00:29:56,470 --> 00:29:57,450
This is the interesting question.

534
00:29:57,450 --> 00:30:03,230
What are the chances that Jesus would fulfill all 191 prophecies exactly?

535
00:30:04,290 --> 00:30:05,330
It's outrageous.

536
00:30:07,060 --> 00:30:09,840
Unless God did it.

537
00:30:11,780 --> 00:30:13,960
I'll end with this quote.

538
00:30:15,130 --> 00:30:21,710
Bertrand Russell, the famous atheist, was basically asked, you know,

539
00:30:22,170 --> 00:30:24,980
what would you say if you stood before God?

540
00:30:26,990 --> 00:30:31,750
And he said something to the effect of, I would say I was never given enough evidence.

541
00:30:32,590 --> 00:30:34,510
Not enough evidence to believe in him.

542
00:30:34,810 --> 00:30:42,300
There was a Look magazine article, and Dr. Russell was asked this question.

543
00:30:42,420 --> 00:30:46,900
Under what condition would you believe in heaven, or in God, sorry.

544
00:30:47,750 --> 00:30:49,050
And he responded with this comment.

545
00:30:49,050 --> 00:30:55,450
He said, quote, if I heard a voice from heaven, and it predicted a series of things, and they came to pass,

546
00:30:56,090 --> 00:31:00,030
then I guess I'd have to believe there was some kind of supernatural being.

547
00:31:02,250 --> 00:31:03,890
Now, think about that for a minute.

548
00:31:05,660 --> 00:31:08,860
Dr. Geisler, years later, responds to that quote by saying this,

549
00:31:09,180 --> 00:31:11,640
Mr. Russell, there has been a voice from heaven,

550
00:31:12,360 --> 00:31:14,320
and it predicted many things,

551
00:31:15,660 --> 00:31:17,300
and they came about to pass.

552
00:31:22,610 --> 00:31:24,750
All those predictions came true.

553
00:31:27,210 --> 00:31:29,750
Mr. Russell, maybe you weren't paying attention.

554
00:31:32,080 --> 00:31:33,500
Or I would even push it further,

555
00:31:33,500 --> 00:31:36,580
because, you know, in my experience with sharing sometimes evidence

556
00:31:36,580 --> 00:31:38,040
for the Bible or for God,

557
00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:41,020
I found an interesting phenomenon that takes place.

558
00:31:41,700 --> 00:31:44,420
I will never forget one of my conversations back in college.

559
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:47,660
This young man and I were talking, and he would come to me every week,

560
00:31:47,700 --> 00:31:49,540
and he had a new challenge about Christianity.

561
00:31:49,700 --> 00:31:51,380
Why it was wrong, why it couldn't be true,

562
00:31:51,740 --> 00:31:53,840
why Jesus was not the Messiah, those kinds of things.

563
00:31:54,260 --> 00:31:56,100
And each week, I would take his question,

564
00:31:56,440 --> 00:31:58,540
and I'd run off, and I would do my research, and I'd come back.

565
00:31:58,580 --> 00:32:00,480
And this went on for, you know, a number of months.

566
00:32:00,940 --> 00:32:04,820
And I would lay out an intellectually credible answer each and every time

567
00:32:04,820 --> 00:32:08,080
for why God, why the Bible, why Jesus, and so forth.

568
00:32:08,460 --> 00:32:10,440
And each time, there was, well, what about this?

569
00:32:11,240 --> 00:32:20,880
After seven, eight, ten times of doing this, I finally asked him, how many more questions do I have to answer before you will make up your mind?

570
00:32:22,250 --> 00:32:30,400
Is it two more? Is it the next one? Or is it 25 more? Or are you never going to believe because you don't want to?

571
00:32:32,200 --> 00:32:35,260
And the issue often, friends, comes down to the issue of the will.

572
00:32:36,660 --> 00:32:41,940
Because deep down, if you really take this data seriously, then you have to believe.

573
00:32:41,940 --> 00:32:43,040
and if you have to believe,

574
00:32:43,140 --> 00:32:46,140
you have to subsume our will to God's will,

575
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:48,480
realizing that we are not the owners of our lives

576
00:32:48,480 --> 00:32:49,500
and we are accountable

577
00:32:49,500 --> 00:32:52,720
and held morally accountable to a higher being.

578
00:32:54,920 --> 00:32:56,440
So I just would put that out there

579
00:32:56,440 --> 00:32:57,520
as one of those things where

580
00:32:57,520 --> 00:32:59,540
if your friend is really seeking,

581
00:32:59,660 --> 00:33:00,820
you can answer those questions

582
00:33:00,820 --> 00:33:01,960
and I think we need to do that.

583
00:33:02,040 --> 00:33:03,540
We need to show intellectual teeth.

584
00:33:03,660 --> 00:33:05,640
We need to show reasons for our faith

585
00:33:05,640 --> 00:33:06,620
because there are reasons

586
00:33:06,620 --> 00:33:08,700
but also don't get caught in the trap

587
00:33:08,700 --> 00:33:09,900
of chasing the wind

588
00:33:09,900 --> 00:33:11,580
when their issue is the will

589
00:33:11,580 --> 00:33:13,500
and not the evidence.

590
00:33:13,540 --> 00:33:16,400
and just be discerning about that

591
00:33:16,400 --> 00:33:18,410
and ask them the question.

592
00:33:18,490 --> 00:33:19,350
We'll take one more question.

593
00:33:19,450 --> 00:33:20,410
This will be it, last question.

594
00:33:20,510 --> 00:33:21,810
If I answer this, you're a Christian, right?

595
00:33:22,310 --> 00:33:23,050
Do it with a smile.

596
00:33:23,190 --> 00:33:23,690
See what happens.

597
00:33:24,530 --> 00:33:25,270
If I answer this question,

598
00:33:25,350 --> 00:33:26,550
you're going to bow down right now, right?

599
00:33:27,010 --> 00:33:27,790
Watch what they say.

600
00:33:28,350 --> 00:33:29,650
You'll figure out where their heart is at.

601
00:33:31,010 --> 00:33:32,330
Friends, I just want to conclude by saying

602
00:33:32,330 --> 00:33:34,490
there's great evidence for the reliability of Scripture

603
00:33:34,490 --> 00:33:37,330
that you can stand on this as the word of truth

604
00:33:37,330 --> 00:33:42,740
and you also can stand on the fact

605
00:33:42,740 --> 00:33:44,940
that God of the Old Testament and the New Testament

606
00:33:44,940 --> 00:33:46,620
is consistent.

607
00:33:46,620 --> 00:33:48,940
that there's judgment and there's mercy in both.

608
00:33:49,920 --> 00:33:51,440
Don't be afraid of what you read.

609
00:33:51,840 --> 00:33:53,960
Study it, and you'll see it to be true.

610
00:33:54,440 --> 00:33:55,400
God is a loving God.

611
00:33:57,330 --> 00:33:58,650
I'm going to pray in just a moment.

